# Constitution — `<project-slug>`

5-15 non-negotiable principles that govern all work in this project. Loaded into every Claude session that touches this repo. Override only via formal RFC.

## Article I — Test-First Imperative (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

Every functional change must ship with a test that fails before the change and passes after. Agents that delete or disable tests to make CI green are violating this article and their work must be rejected.

## Article II — Library-First

Prefer well-maintained existing libraries over custom implementations. Custom code requires explicit justification in the relevant ADR before being written.

## Article III — Contract-Before-Code

All API endpoints, event schemas, and persistent data models must be defined in `spec/<feature>/contracts/` BEFORE implementation. Workers consume the contracts; implementations conform to them, not the other way around.

## Article IV — Bounded-Context Isolation

A single task may modify files in exactly one bounded context (see `PROJECT.json#bounded_contexts`). Cross-context changes must be split into one task per affected context.

## Article V — Atomic Tasks

Every task in `tasks.json` declares `files_owned`, `dependencies`, `acceptance_test`, `parallelizable`, `bounded_context`, `risk_score`. No exceptions. The validator at `scripts/validate-project-spec.py` enforces this.

## Article VI — Files-Owned Non-Overlap

Two tasks with `parallelizable: true` in the same dependency wave MUST NOT share any `files_owned` entries. Enforced at insertion time by `planner-decompose.py`.

## Article VII — One MR per Feature

Workers produce patches that the merge-coordinator assembles into ONE MR per feature. Workers MUST NOT open MRs directly.

